CHECK:BIT_MACRO: Prefer using the BIT macro
#59: FILE: kernel/pid.c:29:
+#define PIDHASH_SIZE (1 << PIDHASH_SHIFT)

Defines like: 1 << <digit> could be BIT(digit).
The BIT() macro is defined via include/linux/bits.h::

  #define BIT(nr)         (1UL << (nr))

CHECK:MACRO_ARG_PRECEDENCE: Macro argument 'nr' may be better as '(nr)' to avoid precedence issues
#60: FILE: kernel/pid.c:30:
+#define pid_hashfn(nr, type) hash_long(nr * PIDTYPE_MAX + type, PIDHASH_SHIFT)

